Гаррі сильніше притиснув паличку до невеличкої секції ґумки, і намагався побачити
крізь ілюзію, яку ненауковці вважали дійсністю, крізь світ столів та стільців,
повітря, ґумок та людей.

// 5768
//When you walked through a park, the immersive world that surrounded you was
//something that existed inside your own brain as a pattern of neurons firing.
//The sensation of a bright blue sky wasn’t something high above you, it was
//something in your visual cortex, and your visual cortex was in the back of your
//brain. All the sensations of that bright world were really happening in that
//quiet cave of bone you called your skull, the place where __you__ lived
//and never, ever left. If you really wanted to say hello to someone, to the
//__actual person,__ you wouldn’t shake their hand, you’d knock gently on
